#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code postfix expression ko evaluate karne ke liye stack use karta hai.

1. Array ke har token ko ek-ek karke traverse karte hain.
2. Agar token number hai, to usse integer me convert karke stack me push kar do.
3. Agar token operator hai, to stack se top ke 2 numbers nikaalte hain:
   - second pop = second operand
   - first pop = first operand
4. Fir operator ke according result nikaalte hain:
   - + → addition
   - - → subtraction
   - * → multiplication
   - / → division
   - ^ → power
5. Jo result aata hai, usse dobara stack me push kar dete hain.
6. End me stack me jo last value bachegi wahi final answer hota hai.

Main idea:
Postfix me operator hamesha apne operands ke baad aata hai,
isliye operator milte hi stack ke top ke 2 values par operation perform kar dete hain.

Important:
Operand order maintain karna bahut zaroori hai:
first operator second
isliye pehla pop second operand hota hai aur doosra pop first operand.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.Deque;
import java.util.ArrayDeque;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution
{

    public boolean isOperator(String s){
      return s.equals("+") || s.equals("-") || s.equals("*") || s.equals("/") || s.equals("^");
    }

    public int evalPostfix(String[] A)
    {
        //You can code here
        
        ArrayDeque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();

        for(String token : A){
          if(isOperator(token)){
            int second = stack.pop();
            int first = stack.pop();
            int result = 0;

            switch(token){
              case "+":
                result = first + second;
                break;
              case "-":
                result = first - second;
                break;
              case "*":
                result = first * second;
                break;
              case "/":
                result = first / second;
                break;
              case "^":
                result = (int)Math.pow(first, second);
                break;
            }
            stack.push(result);
          }
          else{
            //else it is an operand: a number
            stack.push(Integer.parseInt(token));
          }
        }
        return stack.pop();
    }
}
